### 4. Striking, Unusual, or Remarkable Aspects of the Case  
Several elements of the case stand out as extraordinary:  
1. **The Tragic Backdrop of Transgender Suicides**: The Court explicitly referenced the **suicides of Louise Chan (2004) and Sasha Moon (2004)**, two transgender women in Hong Kong who died by suicide after facing public humiliation and discrimination. This contextualized the case as **not merely legal but a matter of life and death**, underscoring the urgency of the Court’s ruling.  
